    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Open surgery for aneurysmal aortic disease can lead to cardiac, renal, pulmonary or muscular
      complications, essentially due to the aortic clamping. Ischemic preconditioning can be useful
      in order to decrease these complications. The investigators would like to use an ischemic
      preconditioning protocol during open surgery of aortic aneurysm in order to decrease these
      complications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
